The paper discusses optimization techniques for Binarized Neural Networks (BNNs) and their performance on image classification tasks such as CIFAR-10 and ImageNet. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper introduces a new optimizer specifically designed for BNNs, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the interpretation of latent weights in BNNs, which could fall under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.THE) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on image classification tasks could also place it under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL), as image classification is a form of visual language processing.
